Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is lightly covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and very faint traces of at least four lines of black-painted Greek text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393875) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393875)
